    <h2 id="aboutAuthor">About Charles Bruckerhoff</h2>
    
    <div id="authorBio"><p>Charles Bruckerhoff&#39;s work in firearms education includes teaching basic pistol courses  and curriculum development and program evaluation for safety training. </p>

<p>His personal interests in the shooting sports include skeet and trap shooting, hunting upland game birds, small game, and big game. He goes away on saltwater fishing excursions whenever time permits. Charles is a Life Member at a local sportsmen&#39;s club, NRA Endowment Life Member and a gun collector. </p>

<p>As a younger man he served in the 31st Combat Engineer Battalion of the U.S. Army in Vietnam. </p>

<p>In addition to firearms, Charles studies American history from the voyages of discovery onward. He visits museums and archives to see first-hand the places where important events unfolded. His library is filled with books written by eye witnesses of events in American history, the great naturalists - Emerson, Thoreau, Burroughs, Muir, Leopold and Olson and classical literature in America, Europe, and Asia.</p>

<p>He&#39;s also a quilter.</p></div>
